  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1413790/extras/2551fa7c0d130fd64aa83c938686fd98.webp?t=1602773705\" width=180 height=50 /></span><br><strong>10mg</strong> is a collection of 10 minute long games.<br><br><strong>HANDMADEDEATHLABYRINTH issue 0</strong> is one of them: an unforgiving little adventure full of monsters that should take about 10 minutes to finish. From start to end, you'll get a specific, singular expression of the dungeon crawl experience; the hero's journey is to descend into the depths, ignoring their fears, and return a different person. What will you find down there?<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1413790/extras/e6d5f3e62954bca85cbdab83e04ba9bb.webp?t=1602773705\" width=400 height=60 /></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >What you'll find in the labyrinth</h2><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> One sword.<br></li><li> One dungeon to crawl that stays the same every time you die.<br></li><li> Anything else you find down there, you keep.</li></ul>",
